{"title_page": "Gimli Film Festival", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=September 2015}}\n[[File:GFF Logo.jpg|thumb|Gimli Film Festival]]\n\nThe '''Gimli Film Festival''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] international film festival, held annually in [[Gimli, Manitoba]].  It is Manitoba's largest film festival, showcasing a mix of [[Narrative film|narrative]], [[Documentary film|documentary]] and [[Experimental film|experimental]] [[feature film]]s and [[short films]]. In 2019, the festival will take place Wednesday, July 24 - Sunday, July 28.\n\n==History==\nThe Gimli Film Festival began in 2001 in [[Gimli, Manitoba]], just one hour north of [[Winnipeg]]. The festival takes place annually on the last weekend of July and has grown to include four indoor venues, industry workshops and events, an annual $10,000 emerging filmmaker pitch competition, a 48 Hour Filmmaking Challenge, and a variety of awards and parties.  The festival is also known for its free outdoor beach film screenings, where films are projected on an 11-meter-tall screen erected annually in the waters of [[Lake Winnipeg]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gimlifilm.com/films/beach-films/|title=Gimli Film Festival {{!}}   RBC Beach Films|website=gimlifilm.com|language=en-CA|access-date=2017-11-28}}</ref>\n\nThe Festival was founded in part by former Senator [[Janis Johnson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/manitoba/manitoba-senator-janis-johnson-retires-1.3774397|title=Conservative Senator Janis Johnson retires after 26 years|publisher=CBC News|date=September 22, 2016|accessdate=October 29, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.gimlifilm.com Gimli Film Festival] Website\n\n[[Category:Film festivals in Manitoba]]\n[[Category:Gimli, Manitoba]]\n[[Category:Film festivals established in 2001]]\n[[Category:Annual events in Manitoba]]\n\n\n{{Canada-festival-stub}}\n{{film-festival-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=September 2015}}\n[[File:GFF Logo.jpg|thumb|Gimli Film Festival]]\n\nThe '''Gimli Film Festival''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] international film festival, held annually in [[Gimli, Manitoba]].  It is Manitoba's largest film festival, showcasing a mix of [[Narrative film|narrative]], [[Documentary film|documentary]] and [[Experimental film|experimental]] [[feature film]]s and [[short films]]. In 2019, the festival will take place Wednesday, July 24 - Sunday, July 28.\n\n==History==\nThe Gimli Film Festival began in 2001 in [[Gimli, Manitoba]], just one hour north of [[Winnipeg]]. The festival takes place annually on the last weekend of July and has grown to include four indoor venues, industry workshops and events, an annual $10,000 emerging filmmaker pitch competition, a 48 Hour Filmmaking Challenge, and a variety of awards and parties.  The festival is also known for its free outdoor beach film screenings, where films are projected on an 11-meter-tall screen erected annually in the waters of [[Lake Winnipeg]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gimlifilm.com/films/beach-films/|title=Gimli Film Festival {{!}}   RBC Beach Films|website=gimlifilm.com|language=en-CA|access-date=2017-11-28}}</ref>\n\nThe Festival was founded in part by former Senator [[Janis Johnson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/manitoba/manitoba-senator-janis-johnson-retires-1.3774397|title=Conservative Senator Janis Johnson retires after 26 years|publisher=CBC News|date=September 22, 2016|accessdate=October 29, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.gimlifilm.com Gimli Film Festival] Website\n\n[[Category:Film festivals in Manitoba]]\n[[Category:Gimli, Manitoba]]\n[[Category:Film festivals established in 2001]]\n\n\n{{Canada-festival-stub}}\n{{film-festival-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ottawa-bio", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added Category:Annual events in Manitoba", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gimli_Film_Festival"}
